description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Simulation Technician, Band 3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting new 1 year fixed term contract, based in our Learning and Development team here at Somerset Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to provide effective and efficient delivery of technician support to a wide range of multi professional pre-registration student simulations and training sessions. As well as support for bespoke sessions and other health care teaching and assessments. They will be expected to liaise with academic, administration and clinical staff across different faculties in the planning and delivery of training activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post involves regular travel to and between sites across Somerset, 3 – 5 times per week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will combine technical and manual skills to look after and move clinical skills equipment and manikins for teaching and learning. They will need to work closely with our Practice Facilitator team and other clinical teams from across the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will require a high level of interpersonal and communication skills; verbal, written and non-verbal. Successful candidate will be working as part of team and independently to flexibly cover the workload and service need. They will also have a passion and aptitude for working with computers and technology and enjoy problem solving.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working days are normally 08:30 till 16:30. No regular weekend or evening sessions but there maybe expectations when needed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Simulation might be a completely new term &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; and you &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;may want to find out some more information about this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Please feel free to email any question relating to this job or &lt;/span&gt;subsequent tasks&lt;span&gt; to myself, or to &lt;/span&gt;discuss our training Sim Suite, the equipment and software that you would be using as well as ask any further questions. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ben Hester, Trust Simulation Facilitator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ben.hester@somersetft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07880 172716&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please be aware that this mobile number is only on during office hours 09:00-16:30&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
